Parents of pupils at Brackenfell High school in Cape Town have clashed with members of the EFF. The party has been demonstrating outside the school over alleged racism at the institution. eNCA's Ronald Masinda has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - There has been widespread condemnation for violent clashes outside Brackenfell High School on Monday. Parents clashed with members of the EFF. The red berets have been demonstrating outside the school over alleged racism, that's after an apparent whites-only matric function was held at the school. READ:Â One suspect arrested at Brackenfell High School protest But parents say a small group of friends organised a private event and no racism was involved. Parliament's Portfolio Committee on Education and the Western Cape Education department have condemned the clashes. Some community members were unimpressed with the EFFs protest.